dct_title_s: Geologic map of the Black Mountain quadrangle, Los Angeles and Ventura Counties, California
dct_description_sm: by Thomas W. Dibblee, Jr.; edited by John A. Minch.
Relief shown by contours and spot heights.
"Topographic base map from newest available USGS 7.5-minute quadrangle, BLACK MOUNTAIN, CA 1995, NIMA 2352 I SW-Series V895".
"Prepared in cooperation with the Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History and the Angeles National Forest".
Includes quadrangle location map, index to adjacent 7.5 minute quadrangles, and index to sources of geology.
